headline: Waste Management (WM) Stock Drops After Earnings
summary: Waste Management (NYSE: WM) missed on both earnings and revenue in Q3, posting adjusted EPS of $1.49 against expectations of $2.08 and revenue of $6.44B versus $6.70B estimated. The stock fell 2.35% in after-hours trading, though the decline was modest given the magnitude of the misses. The real pressure comes from guidance. Management now expects ... headline: Waste Management (NYSE:WM) Reports Sales Below Analyst Estimates In Q3 Earnings
summary: Waste management services provider Waste Management (NYSE:WM) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, but sales rose 14.9% year on year to $6.44 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.98 per share was 1.6% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
